one_apply:

@[simp, to_additive]
theorem one_apply (G H : CommGroupCat) (g : G) : (1 : «expr ⟶ » G H) g = 1 :=
  rfl
#align one_apply one_apply
of_hom_apply:

theorem int_hom_ext {G : AddCommGroupCat.{0}} (f g : «expr ⟶ » (AddCommGroupCat.of ℤ) G) (w : f (1 : ℤ) = g (1 : ℤ)) :

injective_of_mono:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ≫ » -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ≫ » -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⟶ » -/
-- TODO: this argument should be generalised to the situation where
-- the forgetful functor is representable.
theorem injective_of_mono {G H : AddCommGroupCat.{0}} (f : «expr ⟶ » G H) [Mono f] : function.injective f :=
  fun g₁ g₂ h =>
  by
  have t0 : «expr ≫ » (as_hom g₁) f = «expr ≫ » (as_hom g₂) f :=
    by
    ext
    simpa [as_hom_apply] using h
  have t1 : as_hom g₁ = as_hom g₂ := (cancel_mono _).1 t0
  apply as_hom_injective t1
#align injective_of_mono injective_of_mono
ext:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⟶ » -/
@[ext, to_additive]
theorem ext (G H : CommGroupCat) (f₁ f₂ : «expr ⟶ » G H) (w : ∀ x, f₁ x = f₂ x) : f₁ = f₂ :=
  by
  ext1
  apply w
#align ext ext
coe_of:
@[simp, to_additive]
theorem coe_of (R : Type u) [CommGroup R] : (CommGroupCat.of R : Type u) = R :=
  rfl
#align coe_of coe_of
as_hom_injective:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⟶ » -/
theorem as_hom_injective {G : AddCommGroupCat.{0}} : function.injective (@asHom G) := fun h k w => by
  convert congr_arg (fun k : «expr ⟶ » (AddCommGroupCat.of ℤ) G => (k : ℤ → G) (1 : ℤ)) w <;> simp
#align as_hom_injective as_hom_injective
as_hom_apply:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr • » -/
-- This example verifies an improvement possible in Lean 3.8.
-- Before that, to have `monoid_hom.map_map` usable by `simp` here,
-- we had to mark all the concrete category `has_coe_to_sort` instances reducible.
-- Now, it just works.
-- Note that because `ℤ : Type 0`, this forces `G : AddCommGroup.{0}`,
-- so we write this explicitly to be clear.
-- TODO generalize this, requiring a `ulift_instances.lean` file
@[simp]
theorem as_hom_apply {G : AddCommGroupCat.{0}} (g : G) (i : ℤ) : (asHom g) i = «expr • » i g :=
  rfl
#align as_hom_apply as_hom_apply
